notes: Conditional logic via Python control flow

components.name: Analyze Transactions
components.description: Extracts daily transaction CSV files and calculates a risk score for each batch.

components.name: Route Transaction
components.description: Evaluates the risk score and decides whether the transaction batch should go to manual review or autoapproval.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful risk score calculation

components.name: Route to Manual Review
components.description: Sends highrisk transactions (risk_score > 0.8) to the manual review queue for analyst inspection.

upstream_policy.description: Executes only when the branching decision selects the manualreview path

connections.purpose: Load highrisk transactions for human review

components.name: Route to Auto Approve
components.description: Sends lowrisk transactions (risk_score  0.8) to the automated approval system for payment processing.

upstream_policy.description: Executes only when the branching decision selects the autoapprove path

connections.purpose: Load lowrisk transactions for automated payment approval

components.name: Send Notification
components.description: Sends a final notification to the frauddetection team after both manualreview and autoapprove paths have completed.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after both branch paths complete successfully (trigger_rule='none_failed')

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

sources: Daily transaction CSV files stored in the filesystem
sinks: Email notification sent to the fraud detection team
intermediate_datasets: Risk score passed via XCom between analyze_transactions and route_transaction
Messages placed on the manual review queue for highrisk transactions
API calls to the payment processing system for lowrisk transactions
